# Git Flow Configuration for ObsidianForCode

## Branch Strategy

### Main Branches
- **main**: Production-ready code only. Tagged releases only.
- **develop**: Integration branch for features. Active development happens here.

### Supporting Branches
- **feature/xxx**: New features (branch from develop, merge to develop)
- **hotfix/xxx**: Critical fixes (branch from main, merge to both main and develop)
- **release/xxx**: Release preparation (branch from develop, merge to main and develop)

### Development Workflow

1. **Feature Development**:
   ```bash
   git checkout develop
   git checkout -b feature/feature-name
   # Development happens here
   git checkout develop
   git merge --ff-only feature/feature-name
   ```

2. **Release Process**:
   ```bash
   git checkout develop
   git checkout -b release/vX.Y.Z
   # Testing and bug fixes
   git checkout main
   git merge --ff-only release/vX.Y.Z
   git tag vX.Y.Z
   git checkout develop
   git merge --ff-only release/vX.Y.Z
   ```

3. **Hotfix Process**:
   ```bash
   git checkout main
   git checkout -b hotfix/critical-fix
   # Fix implementation
   git checkout main
   git merge --ff-only hotfix/critical-fix
   git tag vX.Y.Z
   git checkout develop
   git merge --ff-only hotfix/critical-fix
   ```

